1
00:00:04,215 --> 00:00:06,315
(Love In Sync)

2
00:00:13,155 --> 00:00:15,625
(Kim Myung Soo)

3
00:00:19,765 --> 00:00:22,295
(Kang Min Ah)

4
00:00:42,015 --> 00:00:45,185
(Love In Sync)

5
00:00:47,025 --> 00:00:48,094
(All people, incidents, and backgrounds...)

6
00:00:48,095 --> 00:00:49,224
(in this drama are fictitious and unrelated to reality.)

7
00:00:49,225 --> 00:00:50,425
(Also, children and animals were filmed under production guidelines.)

8
00:00:50,795 --> 00:00:52,195
Let's do it. The kiss.

9
00:00:52,695 --> 00:00:54,435
How can you suggest a kiss so easily?

10
00:00:55,935 --> 00:00:56,935
You don't know my profession?

11
00:00:57,135 --> 00:00:58,135
I am an actress.

12
00:01:01,935 --> 00:01:03,275
If you run away this time, you are dead.

13
00:01:04,145 --> 00:01:05,175
It is work, just work.

14
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:16,315
Gosh.

15
00:01:18,585 --> 00:01:20,054
Is it right to cast a supporting actor...

16
00:01:20,055 --> 00:01:21,524
through an audition without consulting it...

17
00:01:21,525 --> 00:01:22,855
with the lead actor?

18
00:01:23,295 --> 00:01:25,595
Do I have to consult with you about something like that?

19
00:01:25,925 --> 00:01:26,935
Yes, you do.

20
00:01:27,395 --> 00:01:29,534
If you cast someone who seems to be of a lower calibre,

21
00:01:29,535 --> 00:01:31,465
the lead actor will also appear to be of a lower calibre.

22
00:01:31,835 --> 00:01:33,264
If you cast someone who stands out too much,

23
00:01:33,265 --> 00:01:34,634
our Yi Jin will be overshadowed,

24
00:01:34,635 --> 00:01:36,675
so how can I not worry about that?

25
00:01:37,175 --> 00:01:39,375
Right? And above all,

26
00:01:40,615 --> 00:01:44,415
this is truly not right, is it?

27
00:01:44,885 --> 00:01:46,684
Right? Why is the lead actor...

28
00:01:46,685 --> 00:01:47,954
who stepped down due to a power abuse controversy...

29
00:01:47,955 --> 00:01:50,085
auditioning for a supporting role?

30
00:01:50,255 --> 00:01:53,385
If she wants to audition, is there any reason to stop her?

31
00:01:53,555 --> 00:01:54,594
There is no justification.

32
00:01:54,595 --> 00:01:55,995
We should stop her even if we have to create a justification.

33
00:01:56,595 --> 00:01:58,125
Things are going strangely.

34
00:01:58,425 --> 00:02:00,165
Why are you being so sensitive?

35
00:02:00,535 --> 00:02:02,035
Thanks to this, the movie is getting promoted, which is good.

36
00:02:02,365 --> 00:02:03,664
Without even needing much marketing,

37
00:02:03,665 --> 00:02:05,465
our movie is very popular these days.

38
00:02:05,965 --> 00:02:07,075
That is the problem.

39
00:02:07,735 --> 00:02:09,404
If Ji An, who is merely auditioning for a supporting role,

40
00:02:09,405 --> 00:02:11,804
becomes more popular than our Yi Jin,

41
00:02:11,805 --> 00:02:13,544
she will be overshadowed. It is her first time...

42
00:02:13,545 --> 00:02:14,645
to be the lead actress.

43
00:02:14,915 --> 00:02:15,974
Oh, gosh.

44
00:02:15,975 --> 00:02:17,214
Don't do the audition.

45
00:02:17,215 --> 00:02:19,785
It isn't too late, so cancel that audition.

46
00:02:20,015 --> 00:02:22,585
I'll pick out a good one from my agency.

47
00:02:23,925 --> 00:02:26,785
Mr. Kim, are you going to keep acting like this?

48
00:02:28,625 --> 00:02:29,895
Acting like what?

49
00:02:30,155 --> 00:02:32,264
If you interfere with every little thing and find fault...

50
00:02:32,265 --> 00:02:34,935
throughout the entire film shoot, then I...

51
00:02:35,335 --> 00:02:37,205
cannot work with Han Yi Jin.

52
00:02:38,065 --> 00:02:39,265
Director, it is a misunderstanding.

53
00:02:40,065 --> 00:02:42,374
Our CEO cares about me, so he is acting like this...

54
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:44,675
in case I am intimidated. This will not happen again.

55
00:02:45,575 --> 00:02:47,975
If you are so displeased, then just cancel the contract.

56
00:02:48,445 --> 00:02:49,644
- What? - It isn't too late...

57
00:02:49,645 --> 00:02:50,645
since filming has not started yet.

58
00:02:51,945 --> 00:02:53,655
No, Director Moon.

59
00:02:55,115 --> 00:02:56,115
What?

60
00:02:56,555 --> 00:02:58,325
Anyway, Mr. Kim, you are quite a character.

61
00:02:59,955 --> 00:03:00,955
Me? What?

62
00:03:01,395 --> 00:03:02,494
Let's talk later.

63
00:03:02,495 --> 00:03:04,364
Director Moon.

64
00:03:04,365 --> 00:03:05,365
Please wait.

65
00:03:05,865 --> 00:03:08,265
Anyway, that guy is too arrogant because he is doing well.

66
00:03:12,065 --> 00:03:13,265
Hey.

67
00:03:15,105 --> 00:03:18,244
If you came along, you should be a supporter, not a hindrance.

68
00:03:18,245 --> 00:03:19,545
Why are you silent as a stone?

69
00:03:19,845 --> 00:03:21,844
That's why I told you I wouldn't go along with you from the start.

70
00:03:21,845 --> 00:03:23,315
What's the big deal about a supporting role audition?

71
00:03:23,815 --> 00:03:25,485
Do you know how much I'm struggling because of you?

72
00:03:25,515 --> 00:03:27,285
Frankly, if you just had star power,

73
00:03:28,015 --> 00:03:29,455
would I be doing this humiliating thing?

74
00:03:33,855 --> 00:03:34,855
Look now.

75
00:03:35,755 --> 00:03:36,755
If you search for the movie title on portals,

76
00:03:37,525 --> 00:03:39,424
news about Ji An's supporting role audition comes out first...

77
00:03:39,425 --> 00:03:41,835
before news about you who plays a lead role.

78
00:03:42,295 --> 00:03:43,295
Do you think it makes sense?

79
00:03:43,435 --> 00:03:44,965
That's just buzz.

80
00:03:45,435 --> 00:03:48,075
Buzz is popularity, and popularity is star power.

81
00:03:48,775 --> 00:03:50,605
Something you can never take from Yu Ji An.

82
00:03:51,975 --> 00:03:56,374
I guarantee you, if Ji An gets a role through auditioning,

83
00:03:56,375 --> 00:03:57,615
and joins this film as a supporting actress,

84
00:03:58,115 --> 00:04:00,655
it's only a matter of time before you, the lead, get overshadowed.

85
00:04:01,685 --> 00:04:05,355
So, if you don't want to lose what you just barely took back,

86
00:04:05,755 --> 00:04:06,825
you need to stay focused.

87
00:04:18,835 --> 00:04:19,835
I've made up my mind.

88
00:04:20,305 --> 00:04:21,505
What decision are you talking about?

89
00:04:21,805 --> 00:04:25,644
For a life without regrets, I'll put aside temporary embarrassment.

90
00:04:25,645 --> 00:04:28,075
And I'll do my best with what I can do now.

91
00:04:31,315 --> 00:04:33,445
Oh, no, no. Just now,

92
00:04:33,855 --> 00:04:35,585
I must have misheard you, right?

93
00:04:36,785 --> 00:04:37,785
You heard correctly.

94
00:04:38,185 --> 00:04:39,185
The sound of my heart.

95
00:04:39,285 --> 00:04:40,954
Why are you doing kisses by time of day,

96
00:04:40,955 --> 00:04:42,595
changing locations and weather?

97
00:04:42,825 --> 00:04:44,124
Well, I have no choice.

98
00:04:44,125 --> 00:04:46,564
The audition is coming up soon, and a kiss is definitely...

99
00:04:46,565 --> 00:04:47,995
what causes emotional transference.

100
00:04:48,035 --> 00:04:50,034
Since I could not find any other variable to make it possible,

101
00:04:50,035 --> 00:04:51,935
we have to try everything we can.

102
00:04:57,575 --> 00:04:59,205
Then I will start.

103
00:05:01,975 --> 00:05:03,415
No matter how much I think about it,

104
00:05:04,115 --> 00:05:05,515
this isn't the right thing to do.

105
00:05:05,845 --> 00:05:07,755
There isn't anything else we can do right now.

106
00:05:09,415 --> 00:05:10,585
Still, this is a bit much.

107
00:05:11,455 --> 00:05:12,455
What is it?

108
00:05:12,485 --> 00:05:14,395
Are you perhaps afraid that you will really fall for me?

109
00:05:15,255 --> 00:05:16,255
Oh, well...

110
00:05:18,665 --> 00:05:20,895
- No, I am not. - Then why?

111
00:05:21,365 --> 00:05:23,905
It is business, just work.

112
00:05:26,165 --> 00:05:27,335
Who got the audition?

113
00:05:38,885 --> 00:05:40,285
(Closed)

114
00:06:02,075 --> 00:06:03,175
(Tok Tok Mental Care)

115
00:06:23,755 --> 00:06:26,164
Finally, we succeeded in kissing...

116
00:06:26,165 --> 00:06:28,295
at all hours of the day.

117
00:06:28,895 --> 00:06:31,405
But we failed to reverse the situation.

118
00:06:40,045 --> 00:06:41,345
What should I do?

119
00:06:41,575 --> 00:06:43,175
Today is the day of auditioning, but...

120
00:06:43,675 --> 00:06:44,785
If there is no emotional transference...

121
00:06:46,545 --> 00:06:48,285
You know well about my acting.

122
00:06:48,955 --> 00:06:50,415
Why don't you start practising the acting...

123
00:06:54,855 --> 00:06:56,055
Aren't you thirsty?

124
00:06:56,455 --> 00:06:57,465
Do you want some sparkling water?

125
00:06:57,995 --> 00:06:58,995
I will take it right away.

126
00:07:10,845 --> 00:07:11,845
Please stop it.

127
00:07:14,775 --> 00:07:16,615
Why are you doing this now?

128
00:07:18,515 --> 00:07:19,715
Just leave me alone.

129
00:07:25,225 --> 00:07:26,425
Ji An, are you okay?

130
00:07:30,355 --> 00:07:32,125
(Mom)

131
00:07:33,865 --> 00:07:34,865
Ji An...

132
00:07:35,295 --> 00:07:39,135
actually attempted it before.

133
00:07:39,535 --> 00:07:42,135
There are rumours that it was due to family matters.

134
00:07:42,935 --> 00:07:44,705
There are also rumours that it was because of money.

135
00:08:00,355 --> 00:08:04,365
The first time I lived with my mother...

136
00:08:05,265 --> 00:08:06,525
was when I was seven years old.

137
00:08:08,395 --> 00:08:10,395
Before that, I lived in relatives' houses...

138
00:08:11,305 --> 00:08:12,405
and my maternal grandmother's house.

139
00:08:13,975 --> 00:08:15,835
Then eventually,

140
00:08:17,205 --> 00:08:18,675
she sent me to the orphanage.

141
00:08:20,605 --> 00:08:22,975
Do you know where my mother first took me...

142
00:08:23,575 --> 00:08:25,185
after taking me out of the orphanage?

143
00:08:29,115 --> 00:08:30,684
An audition for child models.

144
00:08:30,685 --> 00:08:32,055
Thank you.

145
00:08:33,455 --> 00:08:34,525
It is funny, right?

146
00:08:34,925 --> 00:08:35,925
Someone said that.

147
00:08:37,365 --> 00:08:39,565
That child models earn a lot of money.

148
00:08:41,165 --> 00:08:43,865
I was pretty even when I was young.

149
00:08:44,835 --> 00:08:47,265
You know, a born natural beauty, right?

150
00:08:52,075 --> 00:08:53,245
I should have been a little less pretty.

151
00:08:56,615 --> 00:08:58,945
Then such a tragedy would not have happened in my life.

152
00:09:01,885 --> 00:09:04,125
Do you know what the biggest tragedy for my mother and me is?

153
00:09:06,225 --> 00:09:08,225
My mother always needs me.

154
00:09:08,925 --> 00:09:12,025
You cannot live as a member of "I Want" forever.

155
00:09:12,925 --> 00:09:15,495
Now is the time to become star Yu Ji An.

156
00:09:16,335 --> 00:09:18,404
Not in a cheap place like this,

157
00:09:18,405 --> 00:09:21,575
we can live in the most luxurious penthouse.

158
00:09:22,405 --> 00:09:23,405
As befits us.

159
00:09:41,825 --> 00:09:43,555
I foolishly loved...

160
00:09:44,365 --> 00:09:46,295
that kind of mother.

161
00:09:50,395 --> 00:09:51,405
Just...

162
00:09:53,805 --> 00:09:56,435
I just wanted to be loved by my mother.

163
00:09:57,545 --> 00:09:59,405
("Idol Group 'I Want' Is Disbanded By Yu Ji An's Leaving")

164
00:10:01,375 --> 00:10:02,575
But one day, I realised.

165
00:10:05,315 --> 00:10:06,315
Is it true?

166
00:10:08,715 --> 00:10:11,025
This isn't the time to be getting my makeup done leisurely.

167
00:10:11,185 --> 00:10:13,985
I had become someone no one loved.

168
00:10:19,095 --> 00:10:20,935
So I ran away with all my might.

169
00:10:25,105 --> 00:10:27,505
I came all this way, fighting for my life.

170
00:10:30,135 --> 00:10:35,175
But you still love your mother so much.

171
00:10:38,985 --> 00:10:39,985
So I am afraid...

172
00:10:42,085 --> 00:10:44,155
that she will appear before me again...

173
00:10:45,055 --> 00:10:46,225
and ruin me.

174
00:10:47,725 --> 00:10:49,425
I am afraid that I will go back to those old days.

175
00:10:50,695 --> 00:10:52,725
If it happens,

176
00:10:54,495 --> 00:10:55,965
I will protect you.

177
00:10:59,735 --> 00:11:00,835
I am your manager.

178
00:11:05,575 --> 00:11:06,645
I am sorry.

179
00:11:07,745 --> 00:11:08,745
Mister.

180
00:11:10,545 --> 00:11:11,945
I always thought about it after that day.

181
00:11:12,515 --> 00:11:14,455
If only I hadn't let go of my sister's hand...

182
00:11:15,055 --> 00:11:16,755
I am the one who made the biggest mistake.

183
00:11:17,585 --> 00:11:19,084
Why am I the only one...

184
00:11:19,085 --> 00:11:20,625
who is perfectly fine?

185
00:11:21,395 --> 00:11:22,595
You must have had a very hard time.

186
00:11:26,725 --> 00:11:27,735
I finally found it.

187
00:11:51,155 --> 00:11:54,125
So, you finally snagged a judge's seat?

188
00:11:54,625 --> 00:11:56,195
Why are you doing this?

189
00:11:56,795 --> 00:11:58,925
I am also a legitimate investor in this film.

190
00:11:59,325 --> 00:12:01,595
I have every right to be in this position.

191
00:12:03,035 --> 00:12:04,035
Isn't that right, Director Moon?

192
00:12:08,935 --> 00:12:11,505
Next, number 358, Yu Ji An, please come in.

193
00:12:25,885 --> 00:12:26,885
Hello.

194
00:12:26,925 --> 00:12:27,925
I am Yu Ji An.

195
00:12:28,255 --> 00:12:29,255
It has been a long time.

196
00:12:29,595 --> 00:12:30,595
You have a performance prepared, right?

197
00:12:31,625 --> 00:12:32,625
Yes.

198
00:12:44,775 --> 00:12:46,044
(What are you talking about?)

199
00:12:46,045 --> 00:12:47,305
(The data is gone? Are you serious right now?)

200
00:12:52,215 --> 00:12:55,215
What? What are you talking about?

201
00:12:56,185 --> 00:12:57,185
The data is gone?

202
00:12:57,585 --> 00:12:58,785
Are you serious right now?

203
00:12:59,755 --> 00:13:01,455
Are you saying she betrayed us?

204
00:13:02,325 --> 00:13:04,025
Gosh, this is driving me crazy.

205
00:13:04,465 --> 00:13:05,865
You don't know what kind of situation we are in right now?

206
00:13:06,765 --> 00:13:07,865
We are almost there.

207
00:13:08,835 --> 00:13:11,605
I am finally able to expose all of her schemes.

208
00:13:13,435 --> 00:13:14,635
But now, betrayal?

209
00:13:15,235 --> 00:13:18,045
Then we are just creating a way for her to escape.

210
00:13:18,645 --> 00:13:20,505
But you are so calm saying that now?

211
00:13:21,475 --> 00:13:22,675
Go find that woman right now.

212
00:13:22,845 --> 00:13:23,845
Somehow, right now.

213
00:13:25,645 --> 00:13:28,015
("Yu Ji An Passes On The Audition, Assuring Her Comeback")

214
00:13:29,255 --> 00:13:30,255
If Ji An gets a role through auditioning,

215
00:13:30,256 --> 00:13:31,525
and joins this film as a supporting actress,

216
00:13:32,155 --> 00:13:34,725
it's only a matter of time before you, the lead, get overshadowed.

217
00:13:50,535 --> 00:13:51,675
Was I that cute?

218
00:13:52,445 --> 00:13:53,945
No, I was not thinking like that.

219
00:13:54,205 --> 00:13:56,275
It is an error of emotional transference. An error.

220
00:13:59,215 --> 00:14:00,715
I told you it was not. It was an error.

221
00:14:01,155 --> 00:14:02,615
Oh, where is the error?

222
00:14:02,655 --> 00:14:03,855
That is perfectly accurate.

223
00:14:03,985 --> 00:14:05,424
Do not misunderstand. There could be such a thing...

224
00:14:05,425 --> 00:14:07,585
as an empathy error. Gosh.

225
00:14:08,095 --> 00:14:09,595
Should we take a picture?

226
00:14:09,895 --> 00:14:10,895
That's great.

227
00:14:11,865 --> 00:14:13,425
Dong Gyeong, please take a picture of us.

228
00:14:14,735 --> 00:14:15,735
Me?

229
00:14:18,835 --> 00:14:20,904
(Congratulations on Yu Ji An's Comeback!)

230
00:14:20,905 --> 00:14:21,905
Okay.

231
00:14:22,975 --> 00:14:23,975
Okay, I will take it.

232
00:14:24,405 --> 00:14:26,905
One, two, three.

233
00:14:32,385 --> 00:14:33,385
I told you it was an error.

234
00:14:33,545 --> 00:14:35,255
- I don't think so. - Okay.

235
00:14:48,935 --> 00:14:50,095
Then go on in.

236
00:14:56,475 --> 00:14:57,575
What was that?

237
00:14:57,805 --> 00:14:59,945
I am not someone who got caught cheating.

238
00:15:11,055 --> 00:15:12,255
There was a call from the real estate agent.

239
00:15:12,825 --> 00:15:14,825
The people who saw the house today want to sign a contract.

240
00:15:15,395 --> 00:15:17,025
I want to sign a contract tomorrow, right away.

241
00:15:17,525 --> 00:15:18,725
- Song Hwan. - You may not know this,

242
00:15:19,225 --> 00:15:21,735
but for someone like me, this kind of house is inconvenient.

243
00:15:23,365 --> 00:15:24,565
Then I will call the real estate agent tomorrow.

244
00:15:25,965 --> 00:15:27,935
When spring comes,

245
00:15:30,535 --> 00:15:31,675
let's move then.

246
00:15:34,645 --> 00:15:36,515
When winter passes and spring comes...

247
00:15:39,215 --> 00:15:40,385
If we leave the house in spring,

248
00:15:44,425 --> 00:15:46,125
I think I will feel less cold.

249
00:16:00,735 --> 00:16:03,404
Gosh, so this was meant to be.

250
00:16:03,405 --> 00:16:04,675
It took a long time to get here.

251
00:16:05,305 --> 00:16:06,605
I look forward to working with you.

252
00:16:07,745 --> 00:16:08,945
I look forward to working with you too.

253
00:16:10,645 --> 00:16:12,414
But how did your acting skills...

254
00:16:12,415 --> 00:16:14,145
improve so much in such a short time?

255
00:16:14,685 --> 00:16:15,685
There is a secret to everything.

256
00:16:21,325 --> 00:16:23,095
Then I can look forward to it.

257
00:16:24,355 --> 00:16:25,365
Of course.

258
00:16:36,235 --> 00:16:38,105
Ha Yul, are you okay?

259
00:16:38,445 --> 00:16:39,645
Gosh.

260
00:16:48,515 --> 00:16:49,614
It hurts.

261
00:16:49,615 --> 00:16:52,785
- Ha Yul. - It hurts.

262
00:17:19,985 --> 00:17:22,655
Stop it. Please stop crying!

263
00:17:40,265 --> 00:17:41,275
What happened, Song Hwan?

264
00:17:42,605 --> 00:17:43,605
He...

265
00:17:45,445 --> 00:17:46,475
abandoned me.

266
00:17:48,815 --> 00:17:50,745
The sound of a child crying...

267
00:17:51,785 --> 00:17:52,845
He said he was sick and tired of her crying.

268
00:17:54,855 --> 00:17:55,855
But Eun Hwan,

269
00:17:57,385 --> 00:17:59,085
I am also so sick and tired of this.

270
00:18:02,895 --> 00:18:06,465
I am so scared of myself.

271
00:18:07,065 --> 00:18:08,065
What should I do?

272
00:18:08,635 --> 00:18:09,635
What should I do about Ha Yul?

273
00:18:10,265 --> 00:18:14,135
Please, please help me.

274
00:18:17,875 --> 00:18:19,405
What should I do about Ha Yul?

275
00:18:19,445 --> 00:18:21,345
It's okay. It's okay, Song Hwan.

276
00:18:22,045 --> 00:18:23,415
I am here for you, right?

277
00:18:34,855 --> 00:18:35,855
Don't worry too much.

278
00:18:37,055 --> 00:18:39,195
Kids just get hurt as they grow up, you know.

279
00:18:43,235 --> 00:18:44,235
Is Ha Yul okay?

280
00:18:45,265 --> 00:18:46,265
Yes, she is okay.

281
00:18:46,805 --> 00:18:47,905
You don't have to worry.

282
00:18:48,005 --> 00:18:49,705
- Is she okay? - Don't...

283
00:18:51,705 --> 00:18:52,745
Don't touch my child.

284
00:18:57,045 --> 00:18:58,285
I was just worried.

285
00:18:58,615 --> 00:18:59,615
Who are you to say that?

286
00:19:00,515 --> 00:19:01,815
By what right?

287
00:19:03,655 --> 00:19:04,655
If it hadn't been for you...

288
00:19:04,656 --> 00:19:07,225
If it hadn't been for someone like you, my father and I...

289
00:19:07,425 --> 00:19:08,525
Song Hwan.

290
00:19:12,365 --> 00:19:14,025
Please.

291
00:19:28,215 --> 00:19:29,315
I am sorry.

292
00:19:30,015 --> 00:19:31,015
Please pass me Ha Yul.

293
00:19:33,385 --> 00:19:34,985
- Please take care of Ji An. - Okay.

294
00:19:39,155 --> 00:19:41,255
Song Hwan is a bit prickly.

295
00:19:44,395 --> 00:19:46,665
We will leave this house as soon as Ha Yul wakes up.

296
00:19:46,965 --> 00:19:47,994
Song Hwan.

297
00:19:47,995 --> 00:19:49,895
I don't want to be treated like baggage by you anymore.

298
00:19:50,795 --> 00:19:51,805
You have done enough, I suppose.

299
00:19:55,435 --> 00:19:58,275
Now, you don't have to be held back by me. Live comfortably.

300
00:19:59,145 --> 00:20:02,315
You are not disabled, not like me.

301
00:20:05,115 --> 00:20:09,055
You hate Ji An, don't you?

302
00:20:12,625 --> 00:20:14,585
Yes, I hate her.

303
00:20:15,255 --> 00:20:16,555
I hate her so much.

304
00:20:17,755 --> 00:20:19,425
Every time I struggle with misfortune,

305
00:20:19,995 --> 00:20:22,065
I'm angry because I feel like it's all her fault.

306
00:20:22,895 --> 00:20:24,064
Every time she smiles in front of me,

307
00:20:24,065 --> 00:20:25,305
pretending she doesn't know anything,

308
00:20:25,705 --> 00:20:27,205
I want to spit on her.

309
00:20:28,275 --> 00:20:29,575
Are you done?

310
00:20:29,635 --> 00:20:30,635
But Song Hwan,

311
00:20:32,245 --> 00:20:33,645
I feel sorry for that woman.

312
00:20:36,215 --> 00:20:38,585
Living with guilt on her back...

313
00:20:40,745 --> 00:20:41,955
It seems like she's similar to me.

314
00:20:46,185 --> 00:20:47,554
I know how suffocating it is to live...

315
00:20:47,555 --> 00:20:52,195
while enduring the gaze of someone who resents me.

316
00:20:56,335 --> 00:20:57,435
I know it best.

317
00:20:59,465 --> 00:21:01,364
- Cha Eun Hwan. - I know.

318
00:21:01,365 --> 00:21:02,435
Song Hwan, I know everything.

319
00:21:03,375 --> 00:21:04,674
That is why I am hesitating.

320
00:21:04,675 --> 00:21:06,175
I stop and will not go any further.

321
00:21:08,845 --> 00:21:09,845
Just three months.

322
00:21:11,375 --> 00:21:12,685
Just three months in this place.

323
00:21:15,315 --> 00:21:16,315
During that period...

324
00:21:19,685 --> 00:21:21,185
Can you please cut me slack?

325
00:21:30,165 --> 00:21:31,165
Cha Eun Hwan.

326
00:21:32,335 --> 00:21:33,765
- What happened? - I don't want to be...

327
00:21:34,165 --> 00:21:35,335
involved with you anymore.

328
00:21:36,505 --> 00:21:39,605
- Is she okay? - Don't touch my child.

329
00:21:40,005 --> 00:21:42,275
Who are you to say that? By what right?

330
00:21:57,695 --> 00:21:59,095
What business do you have with me?

331
00:22:00,225 --> 00:22:01,635
I think I need to know now.

332
00:22:03,335 --> 00:22:05,035
The inexplicable hostility you showed me...

333
00:22:05,765 --> 00:22:08,535
from the first time we met,

334
00:22:09,435 --> 00:22:11,074
and Eun Hwan's mind...

335
00:22:11,075 --> 00:22:13,575
which made him confused while looking at me.

336
00:22:15,275 --> 00:22:16,275
I want to know the reason of them.

337
00:22:18,415 --> 00:22:19,415
Tell me.

338
00:22:19,815 --> 00:22:21,444
What did you mean yesterday when you said...

339
00:22:21,445 --> 00:22:23,155
it was because of me?

340
00:22:23,915 --> 00:22:26,355
Do you really want to know?

341
00:22:36,165 --> 00:22:37,165
It meant nothing.

342
00:22:38,935 --> 00:22:39,935
What?

343
00:22:40,465 --> 00:22:41,735
Yesterday, you clearly said it was because of me.

344
00:22:41,875 --> 00:22:43,305
I was just angry and said whatever came to mind.

345
00:22:44,675 --> 00:22:46,575
I am tired, so please leave.

346
00:23:14,505 --> 00:23:17,105
- Are you alright? - Please save me.

347
00:23:17,435 --> 00:23:19,175
I will definitely save you.

348
00:23:40,325 --> 00:23:41,325
Aren't you getting ready?

349
00:23:42,595 --> 00:23:44,235
Today is the day for your costume fitting.

350
00:23:44,295 --> 00:23:45,764
- Excuse me... - You will be late.

351
00:23:45,765 --> 00:23:47,065
Please get ready quickly.

352
00:24:03,855 --> 00:24:06,724
If I had not touched Father's respirator,

353
00:24:06,725 --> 00:24:09,825
perhaps all this misfortune would have passed us by.

354
00:24:11,095 --> 00:24:12,095
Right.

355
00:24:12,425 --> 00:24:13,625
It cannot be.

356
00:24:14,265 --> 00:24:16,365
I will definitely save you.

357
00:24:17,795 --> 00:24:20,005
I am sorry, mister.

358
00:24:21,035 --> 00:24:22,105
It cannot be.

359
00:24:27,375 --> 00:24:28,415
Yes.

360
00:24:32,645 --> 00:24:33,645
Why? What is it?

361
00:24:36,055 --> 00:24:39,825
Well... Thank you for this morning.

362
00:24:40,525 --> 00:24:41,525
I have no other intentions.

363
00:24:41,925 --> 00:24:43,725
It is just that I hate things getting complicated.

364
00:24:45,025 --> 00:24:47,625
Anyway, all we have to do is leave, right?

365
00:24:50,635 --> 00:24:51,635
It will be spring, right?

366
00:24:53,565 --> 00:24:55,105
If we pretend not to know until then,

367
00:24:55,605 --> 00:24:56,635
then it will be fine, right?

368
00:24:58,945 --> 00:24:59,945
Yes.

369
00:25:01,645 --> 00:25:02,815
Thank you, Song Hwan.

370
00:25:08,655 --> 00:25:09,655
But do you know that?

371
00:25:11,855 --> 00:25:13,885
You are more cruel to Yu Ji An than I am.

372
00:25:16,025 --> 00:25:18,525
You are at least preparing for this,

373
00:25:18,625 --> 00:25:20,594
but from Yu Ji An's perspective, it will feel like she is struck...

374
00:25:20,595 --> 00:25:21,735
by lightning.

375
00:25:23,435 --> 00:25:25,765
She'll feel that miserable feeling,

376
00:25:27,065 --> 00:25:28,135
being abandoned by someone for no reason.

377
00:25:36,575 --> 00:25:37,615
How could...

378
00:25:37,745 --> 00:25:38,745
Both of you...

379
00:25:39,015 --> 00:25:40,015
Right.

380
00:25:41,185 --> 00:25:42,185
Say hello.

381
00:25:42,215 --> 00:25:44,955
This is Manager Cha, who is now my real manager.

382
00:25:51,095 --> 00:25:52,265
I am also suspicious of that.

383
00:25:52,895 --> 00:25:54,595
Because the alibi times match exactly.

384
00:25:55,665 --> 00:25:56,794
Jung In speaks with an excited face,

385
00:25:56,795 --> 00:25:58,235
which does not suit the situation.

386
00:26:01,565 --> 00:26:03,574
Right. It is like he wants...

387
00:26:03,575 --> 00:26:05,345
to play a game with us.

388
00:26:06,275 --> 00:26:07,275
It's making me excited.

389
00:26:08,045 --> 00:26:11,015
It is like he put us into a game that was already set up.

390
00:26:12,145 --> 00:26:14,945
Have you met that woman, his wife, by any chance?

391
00:26:15,715 --> 00:26:19,484
Next, scene 33. Su Ji hears the news of her husband's death...

392
00:26:19,485 --> 00:26:21,625
and cries out like a wailing beast.

393
00:26:23,395 --> 00:26:26,765
Say hello. This is Manager Cha, who is now my real manager.

394
00:26:27,165 --> 00:26:30,464
So, if you don't want to lose what you just barely took back,

395
00:26:30,465 --> 00:26:31,735
you need to stay focused.

396
00:26:37,035 --> 00:26:38,035
No.

397
00:26:38,405 --> 00:26:39,405
That cannot be.

398
00:26:40,645 --> 00:26:41,675
Why my husband?

399
00:26:41,915 --> 00:26:43,415
Who did this?

400
00:26:49,455 --> 00:26:50,785
Detective, please.

401
00:26:52,055 --> 00:26:54,525
Please save my husband.

402
00:26:55,495 --> 00:26:56,795
What should I do?

403
00:26:58,395 --> 00:27:00,625
How should I live now?

404
00:27:15,075 --> 00:27:16,645
I am not intimidated by Yi Jin.

405
00:27:17,145 --> 00:27:18,415
I am worried.

406
00:27:19,545 --> 00:27:20,545
Because tomorrow is my first shoot.

407
00:27:21,145 --> 00:27:22,155
Who said anything?

408
00:27:22,515 --> 00:27:24,055
You just said something.

409
00:27:24,485 --> 00:27:25,485
I heard everything.

410
00:27:27,185 --> 00:27:29,054
You always reveal other people's true feelings...

411
00:27:29,055 --> 00:27:30,325
without permission.

412
00:27:33,095 --> 00:27:34,195
Shall we go to Han River?

413
00:27:36,735 --> 00:27:38,934
Once filming starts, I will not be able to move.

414
00:27:38,935 --> 00:27:40,435
So, we can heal ourselves before then.

415
00:27:42,905 --> 00:27:44,505
You are an actress, and you're not managing your condition?

416
00:27:44,705 --> 00:27:46,075
What if you catch a cold?

417
00:27:46,205 --> 00:27:47,405
It will affect the shoot.

418
00:27:47,645 --> 00:27:49,244
No, who said I would be there for a long time?

419
00:27:49,245 --> 00:27:50,715
Let's get some fresh air for a moment.

420
00:27:51,045 --> 00:27:53,585
What if you get caught up in a baseless rumour like last time?

421
00:27:54,445 --> 00:27:56,484
If you get into a scandal with a manager...

422
00:27:56,485 --> 00:27:58,485
who you have no relationship with,

423
00:27:59,185 --> 00:28:00,525
it won't be good for your image.

424
00:28:02,125 --> 00:28:03,354
Alright. I am not going.

425
00:28:03,355 --> 00:28:04,555
Is that enough?

426
00:28:11,295 --> 00:28:14,835
What kind of relationship do you have with Yi Jin?

427
00:28:15,805 --> 00:28:17,005
Is she someone special to you?

428
00:28:17,935 --> 00:28:20,774
Yi Jin and I are simply a client...

429
00:28:20,775 --> 00:28:22,615
and a counsellor.

430
00:28:24,745 --> 00:28:25,745
Right?

431
00:28:26,285 --> 00:28:27,285
I thought so.

432
00:28:28,015 --> 00:28:31,115
It's just that she was my first client, so it's a bit more special.

433
00:28:33,085 --> 00:28:34,485
Special, my foot.

434
00:28:38,395 --> 00:28:40,125
What did you consult her about?

435
00:28:41,665 --> 00:28:43,395
She didn't seem to be struggling at all.

436
00:28:48,105 --> 00:28:49,105
What is this?

437
00:28:49,135 --> 00:28:50,605
This feeling of being curious about me?

438
00:28:51,235 --> 00:28:52,245
I am just proud of you.

439
00:28:53,205 --> 00:28:54,504
I am so proud of you...

440
00:28:54,505 --> 00:28:56,215
because you're finally curious about such things.

441
00:28:58,745 --> 00:28:59,745
However...

442
00:29:00,715 --> 00:29:02,754
The content of counselling must not be disclosed to others.

443
00:29:02,755 --> 00:29:03,755
That is a counselling principle.

444
00:29:04,955 --> 00:29:07,355
If you are really curious, think about it.

445
00:29:08,425 --> 00:29:10,625
Why a young female celebrity named Han Yi Jin...

446
00:29:11,125 --> 00:29:14,625
came to a counsellor after her group disbanded.

447
00:29:15,095 --> 00:29:16,735
Thinking about such things...

448
00:29:17,235 --> 00:29:18,365
That would be empathy.

449
00:29:43,295 --> 00:29:44,895
Ji An, how about this outfit for today?

450
00:29:45,865 --> 00:29:46,994
It's good.

451
00:29:46,995 --> 00:29:48,065
Should I wear this one next?

452
00:29:48,325 --> 00:29:49,335
Oh, yes, that will be nice.

453
00:29:50,235 --> 00:29:51,235
You know how to cinch the waist here, right?

454
00:29:51,495 --> 00:29:52,534
- Oh, I know, I know. - Like this. Okay.

455
00:29:52,535 --> 00:29:53,705
I know you are pretty, but today you are especially pretty.

456
00:29:53,735 --> 00:29:55,534
- Hello. Yu Ji An from I Want. - Hello.

457
00:29:55,535 --> 00:29:57,075
Would an interview be possible for a moment?

458
00:29:57,375 --> 00:29:58,844
Thank you. Let's move slightly.

459
00:29:58,845 --> 00:30:00,375
We will move slightly.

460
00:30:01,345 --> 00:30:04,415
You've returned with I Want's album with all members this time.

461
00:30:04,715 --> 00:30:06,515
Please say a word to your waiting fans.

462
00:30:08,955 --> 00:30:10,485
Yes, until now, I Want...

463
00:30:10,755 --> 00:30:11,755
Just a moment.

464
00:30:11,885 --> 00:30:13,925
Ji An, could you please do it?

465
00:30:17,295 --> 00:30:19,424
Yes, to all the fans who have waited for us until now,

466
00:30:19,425 --> 00:30:20,795
thank you very much.

467
00:30:21,025 --> 00:30:23,534
We prepared this album very diligently,

468
00:30:23,535 --> 00:30:26,005
so please give us a lot of attention and endless love.

469
00:30:26,335 --> 00:30:29,205
Then, so far, I Want!

470
00:30:29,675 --> 00:30:31,374
- Yes, I Want... Yes, thank you. - Thank you.

471
00:30:31,375 --> 00:30:32,975
Please look forward to I Want's full-group album.

472
00:30:33,075 --> 00:30:34,075
Thank you.

473
00:30:36,075 --> 00:30:39,045
("'I Want' Is Disbanded And Yu Ji An Will Debut As A Solo")

474
00:30:47,325 --> 00:30:48,555
Please walk slowly.

475
00:30:48,825 --> 00:30:49,825
You are walking this fast because it's the first shoot?

476
00:30:50,295 --> 00:30:51,295
Just come with me.

477
00:30:54,625 --> 00:30:56,735
Why are you doing this? You are embarrassing me.

478
00:30:57,735 --> 00:30:58,735
Am I a grade schooler?

479
00:30:59,435 --> 00:31:01,164
You're not an overprotective parent.

480
00:31:01,165 --> 00:31:02,505
What? You're embarrassed?

481
00:31:02,875 --> 00:31:04,905
Hey, why are we doing this for?

482
00:31:07,075 --> 00:31:08,075
Is it because of me?

483
00:31:08,445 --> 00:31:09,645
Of course.

484
00:31:10,875 --> 00:31:13,385
As a rule, no one dislikes it when you feed them.

485
00:31:13,885 --> 00:31:16,785
The one who feeds gets more respect than the one who does not.

486
00:31:17,015 --> 00:31:18,015
That is how life is.

487
00:31:18,855 --> 00:31:19,925
Who knows.

488
00:31:20,725 --> 00:31:22,995
They might even give you an extra reflector over Ji An.

489
00:31:23,495 --> 00:31:25,055
That Ji An is truly something.

490
00:31:26,125 --> 00:31:27,265
Just stay still.

491
00:31:27,325 --> 00:31:28,365
We will take care of everything.

492
00:31:28,795 --> 00:31:30,195
Ji An was also raised this way.

493
00:31:38,905 --> 00:31:40,605
Speak of the devil, and she shall appear.

494
00:31:41,775 --> 00:31:42,875
That is a very good thing.

495
00:31:44,145 --> 00:31:45,615
I like that it isn't obvious.

496
00:31:48,955 --> 00:31:51,185
How is it, being a manager?

497
00:31:52,055 --> 00:31:53,355
It isn't easy, is it?

498
00:31:54,755 --> 00:31:56,155
Not really.

499
00:31:57,655 --> 00:32:00,065
I know everything without you saying it.

500
00:32:01,265 --> 00:32:03,965
Ji An's temper isn't ordinary.

501
00:32:04,495 --> 00:32:06,735
Her capriciousness is also deadly.

502
00:32:07,165 --> 00:32:09,274
Even now, if she isn't in a good mood,

503
00:32:09,275 --> 00:32:10,675
she acts up, doesn't she?

504
00:32:12,105 --> 00:32:14,305
- Not really. - What?

505
00:32:18,215 --> 00:32:19,815
Why have you been speaking informally to me since earlier?

506
00:32:21,715 --> 00:32:22,715
Because you spoke informally to me first?

507
00:32:25,625 --> 00:32:26,885
You seem to care a lot about your actors.

508
00:32:27,355 --> 00:32:29,425
The CEO even comes to the set in person.

509
00:32:30,625 --> 00:32:32,025
Even though I am a CEO of the company,

510
00:32:32,225 --> 00:32:35,195
I care for them with the heart of their fathers'.

511
00:32:36,835 --> 00:32:37,835
As for me,

512
00:32:39,105 --> 00:32:43,105
I truly think of my actors as my own children.

513
00:32:45,235 --> 00:32:46,275
Indeed.

514
00:32:48,305 --> 00:32:50,145
But it seems Ji An was disowned.

515
00:32:52,915 --> 00:32:55,144
No, during the power abuse controversy,

516
00:32:55,145 --> 00:32:56,715
it seemed like you didn't protect her like parents.

517
00:32:57,655 --> 00:32:59,725
There was no attempt to settle with the victim, no media control,

518
00:33:00,225 --> 00:33:01,755
and no legal action at all.

519
00:33:04,155 --> 00:33:05,155
Oh, that was...

520
00:33:05,425 --> 00:33:07,325
The timing was so bad at that time.

521
00:33:07,665 --> 00:33:09,334
She wasn't even our agency's actress anymore,

522
00:33:09,335 --> 00:33:10,635
so what right did I have?

523
00:33:11,095 --> 00:33:12,305
Frankly, what obligation did I have?

524
00:33:13,505 --> 00:33:14,965
Indeed. I also find that very strange.

525
00:33:16,735 --> 00:33:20,004
How such a controversy erupted at a perfect time...

526
00:33:20,005 --> 00:33:21,645
for Ji An to take all the blame alone.

527
00:33:22,715 --> 00:33:26,985
As if someone did it on purpose.

528
00:33:31,715 --> 00:33:33,785
Alright, let's take a picture before the first shoot.

529
00:33:34,055 --> 00:33:35,125
Everyone, please gather around.

530
00:33:35,755 --> 00:33:36,895
Yes, please gather here.

531
00:33:37,495 --> 00:33:38,495
Yes.

532
00:33:41,295 --> 00:33:42,835
Yes, please gather here.

533
00:33:50,875 --> 00:33:54,005
Well... That spot is for the lead actor.

534
00:33:57,315 --> 00:33:58,415
Right.

535
00:34:01,785 --> 00:34:03,185
It has become a habit.

536
00:34:11,325 --> 00:34:12,425
Alright, we are shooting.

537
00:34:13,125 --> 00:34:14,595
One, two, three.

538
00:34:24,505 --> 00:34:26,275
Ready. Action.

539
00:34:28,145 --> 00:34:30,745
What? What did you just say?

540
00:34:32,715 --> 00:34:33,845
What is he doing?

541
00:34:34,485 --> 00:34:36,815
He should be watching Ji An's acting, not the script.

542
00:34:37,485 --> 00:34:38,785
He doesn't have basics down.

543
00:34:39,825 --> 00:34:41,425
What do you want me to do?

544
00:34:43,755 --> 00:34:46,125
I am not an actor who moves according to the script they wrote.

545
00:34:47,325 --> 00:34:49,665
CCTV footage that appears to be Kang Jun Ho has been found.

546
00:34:50,365 --> 00:34:52,605
We both fell for their scheme.

547
00:34:55,165 --> 00:34:56,235
Hang up for now.

548
00:34:57,005 --> 00:35:01,545
Who interfered and how?

549
00:35:03,815 --> 00:35:06,345
It means there is someone in this team helping them.

550
00:35:08,545 --> 00:35:09,755
Cut.

551
00:35:12,115 --> 00:35:13,185
Ji An's emotions are so good.

552
00:35:13,525 --> 00:35:14,885
Oh, really?

553
00:35:15,155 --> 00:35:16,795
Yes. Is this your first shoot, right?

554
00:35:16,895 --> 00:35:17,895
Your immersion is incredible.

555
00:35:19,225 --> 00:35:22,065
- Still, let's try one more take. - Okay.

556
00:35:27,405 --> 00:35:29,235
You saw people were surprised when I was acting earlier, right?

557
00:35:29,635 --> 00:35:32,105
I am telling you I saw it more than ten times.

558
00:35:32,845 --> 00:35:34,005
I even heard Director Moon's praise.

559
00:35:34,605 --> 00:35:37,015
I am also telling you I heard it more than ten times.

560
00:35:40,215 --> 00:35:41,215
Thank you.

561
00:35:42,585 --> 00:35:44,415
This is all thanks to Eun Hwan,

562
00:35:45,115 --> 00:35:47,685
no, Manager Cha.

563
00:35:51,795 --> 00:35:53,025
Should we just sign a lifetime contract?

564
00:35:53,625 --> 00:35:55,094
This time, I will sign a contract with you...

565
00:35:55,095 --> 00:35:56,795
with the best treatment in the industry.

566
00:35:59,435 --> 00:36:02,105
How long are you going to rely on my emotions?

567
00:36:04,235 --> 00:36:05,235
Ji An, you are an actress.

568
00:36:05,975 --> 00:36:08,144
Then you should try to feel your emotions yourself...

569
00:36:08,145 --> 00:36:09,245
and act.

570
00:36:11,915 --> 00:36:13,415
Who says I won't?

571
00:36:14,545 --> 00:36:18,385
I am just grateful, anyway.

572
00:36:18,455 --> 00:36:19,955
Three months.

573
00:36:20,985 --> 00:36:23,024
When that contract period ends,

574
00:36:23,025 --> 00:36:25,055
we will go back to our respective places.

575
00:36:27,295 --> 00:36:28,395
Don't forget that.

576
00:36:40,675 --> 00:36:42,105
Sometimes, I lose my temper, but I don't hold grudges.

577
00:36:43,345 --> 00:36:44,475
Why am I suddenly angry now?

578
00:36:45,075 --> 00:36:46,245
No, I cannot understand.

579
00:36:46,685 --> 00:36:49,085
Ji Woong has a lot of schedules.

580
00:36:49,255 --> 00:36:51,385
Our Ji An also has just as many schedules.

581
00:36:51,785 --> 00:36:53,084
- No. - It isn't polite...

582
00:36:53,085 --> 00:36:55,585
to give one person the first and last scenes.

583
00:36:56,895 --> 00:36:57,925
It was not my anger.

584
00:37:00,025 --> 00:37:01,124
If he's going to act like that behind my back,

585
00:37:01,125 --> 00:37:02,125
why did he act like that in front of me?

586
00:37:06,865 --> 00:37:07,865
Look over there.

587
00:37:08,765 --> 00:37:10,575
I saw it. Why?

588
00:37:11,505 --> 00:37:14,345
That man is my manager.

589
00:37:15,505 --> 00:37:18,144
Are you bragging about your current manager...

590
00:37:18,145 --> 00:37:19,815
in front of your former manager?

591
00:37:20,745 --> 00:37:22,145
Is this EXchange or something?

592
00:37:23,655 --> 00:37:25,315
I won't send you text messages from now on.

593
00:37:27,225 --> 00:37:28,655
I am sorry. Just a moment.

594
00:37:31,125 --> 00:37:32,125
Yes, I am Yu Ji An's manager.

595
00:37:33,165 --> 00:37:35,965
Yes. A commercial?

596
00:37:37,835 --> 00:37:38,835
Oh, yes.

597
00:37:43,405 --> 00:37:45,174
Gosh. How long has it been...

598
00:37:45,175 --> 00:37:46,975
since I smelled the scent of the advertising agency?

599
00:37:47,875 --> 00:37:48,905
Is it that good?

600
00:37:49,045 --> 00:37:50,945
You seem happier than when you were cast in a movie.

601
00:37:51,475 --> 00:37:53,885
This commercial is a measure of popularity.

602
00:37:54,285 --> 00:37:57,315
Among them, only the top of the top can film a shampoo commercial.

603
00:37:58,415 --> 00:38:01,185
And most importantly, the unit price is high.

604
00:38:02,355 --> 00:38:03,395
What?

605
00:38:04,525 --> 00:38:07,695
I need to earn money quickly to lift the provisional attachment.

606
00:38:12,465 --> 00:38:16,335
At one time, all the posters hanging here had my face on them.

607
00:38:20,945 --> 00:38:23,674
Oh, I heard we were doing a test shoot today,

608
00:38:23,675 --> 00:38:26,245
I practised some poses for the first time in a while, so take a look.

609
00:38:26,745 --> 00:38:27,815
Okay.

610
00:38:41,025 --> 00:38:42,435
You are fluttered, right?

611
00:38:42,465 --> 00:38:44,795
No, what nonsense.

612
00:38:45,565 --> 00:38:47,664
– Is it really not true? – I said it isn't.

613
00:38:47,665 --> 00:38:48,665
Is that so?

614
00:38:58,845 --> 00:39:00,115
Your heart is beating so fast.

615
00:39:03,155 --> 00:39:04,215
You fool.

616
00:39:04,785 --> 00:39:06,325
Do you think you can hide it?

617
00:39:07,385 --> 00:39:08,485
What kind of relationship do you think we have?

618
00:39:11,595 --> 00:39:13,365
A relationship where feelings are conveyed.

619
00:39:15,765 --> 00:39:17,595
No matter how mean you are to me,

620
00:39:19,465 --> 00:39:20,465
I wouldn't fall for it.

621
00:39:21,965 --> 00:39:23,705
I know it isn't sincere.

622
00:39:29,215 --> 00:39:30,515
So,

623
00:39:31,675 --> 00:39:36,585
please stop being cold to me on purpose.

624
00:39:38,215 --> 00:39:40,554
I already feel like I am being ostracized...

625
00:39:40,555 --> 00:39:43,225
by everyone in the world these days.

626
00:39:43,395 --> 00:39:44,755
If Eun Hwan does that too,

627
00:39:46,295 --> 00:39:47,595
then I will have nowhere to lean on.

628
00:39:56,505 --> 00:39:58,605
I need to go to the restroom before the meeting.

629
00:39:59,345 --> 00:40:00,375
Wait a moment.

630
00:40:14,585 --> 00:40:15,755
Yes, hello.

631
00:40:17,395 --> 00:40:21,625
We are near there. Right in front... What?

632
00:40:21,995 --> 00:40:23,735
You want to cancel the contract now?

633
00:40:24,335 --> 00:40:26,404
We don't want to do this either, but...

634
00:40:26,405 --> 00:40:28,465
Have you not seen the article yet?

635
00:40:32,675 --> 00:40:33,704
("Brand Loves Her, But Consumers Still Refuse Her")

636
00:40:33,705 --> 00:40:34,705
("Yu Ji An's New Controversy About Her Commercial")

637
00:40:35,545 --> 00:40:37,415
I'm Han Seo Jun, a reporter from the Taejin Sports entertainment desk.

638
00:40:38,015 --> 00:40:39,245
If you have time, let's do a quick interview.

639
00:40:46,525 --> 00:40:49,085
Do you want to go to Han River?

640
00:40:54,295 --> 00:40:55,994
So this is...

641
00:40:55,995 --> 00:40:57,695
It is the Han River for comfort.

642
00:41:01,765 --> 00:41:02,975
It is alright.

643
00:41:03,475 --> 00:41:04,735
You don't have to worry that much.

644
00:41:06,345 --> 00:41:07,705
It isn't like this is the 1st or 2nd time this has happened.

645
00:41:09,475 --> 00:41:12,885
At this point, even wounds...

646
00:41:16,255 --> 00:41:17,985
I don't get used to them.

647
00:41:19,825 --> 00:41:21,555
It still hurts.

648
00:41:24,555 --> 00:41:26,565
Because the truth has not been revealed yet.

649
00:41:27,365 --> 00:41:29,094
When the truth is revealed, then...

650
00:41:29,095 --> 00:41:30,795
What is the...

651
00:41:32,865 --> 00:41:34,035
truth?

652
00:41:36,875 --> 00:41:38,405
Eun Hwan, do you really believe...

653
00:41:39,205 --> 00:41:40,945
I didn't do that?

654
00:41:49,615 --> 00:41:51,285
The Yu Ji An I know...

655
00:41:51,685 --> 00:41:52,925
would never do such a thing.

656
00:41:56,055 --> 00:41:57,225
Gosh.

657
00:41:58,755 --> 00:41:59,865
You're serious.

658
00:42:03,435 --> 00:42:04,735
That's touching.

659
00:42:06,405 --> 00:42:07,905
But what should I do?

660
00:42:09,035 --> 00:42:10,335
I did it.

661
00:42:12,475 --> 00:42:15,145
I was so embarrassed that I didn't want to say this.

662
00:42:16,775 --> 00:42:18,375
That video...

663
00:42:19,415 --> 00:42:20,415
They said it wasn't manipulated.

664
00:42:23,415 --> 00:42:24,715
They said it was the original.

665
00:42:26,455 --> 00:42:27,455
So,

666
00:42:28,725 --> 00:42:30,425
they say I really did that...

667
00:42:31,325 --> 00:42:32,625
to Mi Jeong.

668
00:42:37,335 --> 00:42:38,335
What should I do?

669
00:42:40,135 --> 00:42:41,335
I feel sorry for Mi Jeong.

670
00:42:51,915 --> 00:42:53,215
You have no idea what kind of situation this is...

671
00:42:54,585 --> 00:42:55,585
What is it now?

672
00:42:56,155 --> 00:42:58,255
Are you brutally executing someone who turned themselves in?

673
00:42:59,485 --> 00:43:00,485
Just look at it first.

674
00:43:01,685 --> 00:43:02,795
You have no idea, right?

675
00:43:04,425 --> 00:43:06,425
Oh, this is so frustrating. It is so annoying.

676
00:43:06,925 --> 00:43:08,825
What are all these problems after recruiting a wrong person?

677
00:43:09,935 --> 00:43:10,935
Isn't something a little strange?

678
00:43:11,865 --> 00:43:12,865
What is it?

679
00:43:13,435 --> 00:43:15,304
You know that your language proficiency...

680
00:43:15,305 --> 00:43:17,035
is lacking compared to the general standard, right?

681
00:43:18,135 --> 00:43:20,174
Me? Not at all.

682
00:43:20,175 --> 00:43:21,275
I have never heard that before.

683
00:43:23,215 --> 00:43:24,315
Is that so?

684
00:43:24,445 --> 00:43:26,115
Since you heard it now, keep it in mind from now on.

685
00:43:27,745 --> 00:43:28,944
Someone like Ji An,

686
00:43:28,945 --> 00:43:32,485
who lacks language proficiency and are immature in emotional control,

687
00:43:33,425 --> 00:43:36,595
their words would be all jumbled up when they're angry, but look.

688
00:43:37,695 --> 00:43:40,065
She is speaking so precisely and smoothly, isn't she?

689
00:43:40,325 --> 00:43:41,325
Why are you crying?

690
00:43:41,325 --> 00:43:42,325
Why are you crying?

691
00:43:42,765 --> 00:43:44,964
- Because of you... - It's like she is reciting lines...

692
00:43:44,965 --> 00:43:46,565
from a drama she memorized.

693
00:43:47,005 --> 00:43:49,705
I told you not to cry.

694
00:43:50,775 --> 00:43:52,304
Did you practice lines with Mi Jeong...

695
00:43:52,305 --> 00:43:53,805
a lot in the past?

696
00:43:55,445 --> 00:43:56,775
Almost every project.

697
00:44:00,185 --> 00:44:01,715
So, what you're saying is...

698
00:44:02,545 --> 00:44:04,915
I was not actually abusing my power in the video,

699
00:44:05,915 --> 00:44:07,285
but practising lines?

700
00:44:08,085 --> 00:44:10,294
And Mi Jeong maliciously edited it...

701
00:44:10,295 --> 00:44:12,495
and uploaded it as an abuse of power video?

702
00:44:14,725 --> 00:44:15,825
Probably.

703
00:44:16,495 --> 00:44:18,035
No, why?

704
00:44:19,095 --> 00:44:22,005
Why would Mi Jeong do that to me?

705
00:44:23,005 --> 00:44:24,305
I don't know.

706
00:44:24,735 --> 00:44:27,045
We will only know for sure after meeting her.

707
00:44:28,445 --> 00:44:30,415
It could be for her own personal goal.

708
00:44:31,575 --> 00:44:34,815
Or it could be that she was paid by someone...

709
00:44:35,745 --> 00:44:37,615
who wants Ji An to fall.

710
00:44:41,555 --> 00:44:42,855
Can you even think?

711
00:44:43,425 --> 00:44:45,455
You have no idea what kind of situation this is, do you?

712
00:44:46,965 --> 00:44:49,994
The video isn't manipulated, so the situation cannot be false.

713
00:44:49,995 --> 00:44:51,664
What are all these problems after recruiting a wrong person?

714
00:44:51,665 --> 00:44:54,235
What cases are there where it isn't the truth?

715
00:44:54,465 --> 00:44:55,504
Hey.

716
00:44:55,505 --> 00:44:57,435
I am genuinely curious, so I am asking you.

717
00:44:57,935 --> 00:44:59,475
Does your family know you act like this?

718
00:45:01,045 --> 00:45:02,545
Oh, look at her.

719
00:45:03,275 --> 00:45:04,275
Are you crying?

720
00:45:04,276 --> 00:45:07,385
Hey, why are you crying?

721
00:45:07,785 --> 00:45:09,785
Who should be crying because of you right now?

722
00:45:11,115 --> 00:45:12,155
Don't cry.

723
00:45:12,415 --> 00:45:13,655
I told you not to cry.

724
00:45:17,225 --> 00:45:19,865
(Universe in the Room)

725
00:45:23,195 --> 00:45:25,034
I received the call and checked.

726
00:45:25,035 --> 00:45:26,835
The Universe in the Room was an independent film.

727
00:45:27,165 --> 00:45:28,435
An independent film?

728
00:45:29,505 --> 00:45:31,335
A top star like Ji An?

729
00:45:31,805 --> 00:45:37,645
Back then, she was pretending to be artsy for a long time,

730
00:45:38,345 --> 00:45:40,644
so she made many special appearances in independent films...

731
00:45:40,645 --> 00:45:43,515
to build up her acting skills and to transform her image.

732
00:45:43,755 --> 00:45:45,484
But why can't I find any information about the film...

733
00:45:45,485 --> 00:45:46,485
when I search for it?

734
00:45:46,925 --> 00:45:47,925
There is no way you would find any.

735
00:45:48,485 --> 00:45:49,625
The production was cancelled early on.

736
00:45:50,225 --> 00:45:51,225
So, there is no data.

737
00:45:52,655 --> 00:45:53,665
Is that so?

738
00:45:54,925 --> 00:45:57,595
Then what about the script she received at the time?

739
00:45:58,265 --> 00:45:59,365
That's gone too.

740
00:46:00,165 --> 00:46:01,564
I don't know about anything else,

741
00:46:01,565 --> 00:46:03,275
but one thing I remember clearly is this.

742
00:46:03,575 --> 00:46:05,604
They were worried the script would be leaked,

743
00:46:05,605 --> 00:46:08,175
so they only sent the parts Ji An appeared through quick service.

744
00:46:08,945 --> 00:46:10,815
However...

745
00:46:11,475 --> 00:46:12,985
Why are you so curious about that movie?

746
00:46:15,745 --> 00:46:18,055
- It's nothing. - Okay.

747
00:46:19,285 --> 00:46:20,885
I will be going now.

748
00:46:25,195 --> 00:46:26,195
What are you doing?

749
00:46:27,025 --> 00:46:28,025
Do Hoon.

750
00:46:29,325 --> 00:46:31,235
Isn't the stigma of being a traitor...

751
00:46:31,735 --> 00:46:34,535
- difficult for you? - What?

752
00:46:35,365 --> 00:46:40,005
You are someone who cares about Ji An.

753
00:46:43,015 --> 00:46:45,045
Can you see it, Counsellor?

754
00:46:46,175 --> 00:46:47,185
That mind toward her?

755
00:46:48,445 --> 00:46:49,855
I am a psychological counsellor, you know.

756
00:46:50,815 --> 00:46:53,454
That is why I want to give you...

757
00:46:53,455 --> 00:46:55,655
a chance to clear your name...

758
00:46:56,155 --> 00:46:58,095
from the stigma of being a traitor.

759
00:47:00,265 --> 00:47:01,265
Give it to me.

760
00:47:17,145 --> 00:47:18,145
What are you doing?

761
00:47:18,275 --> 00:47:20,585
Oh, yes. I dropped a coin.

762
00:47:21,015 --> 00:47:22,015
Where did it go?

763
00:47:25,455 --> 00:47:26,455
This was yours.

764
00:47:27,125 --> 00:47:29,485
It's good to be thrifty. Right.

765
00:47:31,425 --> 00:47:32,425
Hey, Manager!

766
00:47:33,595 --> 00:47:36,335
You found my coin, so I will buy you a drink.

767
00:47:37,095 --> 00:47:38,095
How about it?

768
00:47:38,495 --> 00:47:40,304
- That's good. - Oh, yes.

769
00:47:40,305 --> 00:47:41,735
- Let's go. - Let's go.

770
00:47:46,305 --> 00:47:47,675
So...

771
00:47:48,675 --> 00:47:51,945
Is there only one you found out? The film director's name?

772
00:47:52,415 --> 00:47:53,484
I tried contacting the Film Commission...

773
00:47:53,485 --> 00:47:55,014
and the Independent Film Association,

774
00:47:55,015 --> 00:47:56,615
but they don't have his contact information.

775
00:47:57,285 --> 00:48:00,355
Of all people, that film director's name is Kim Min Su.

776
00:48:00,985 --> 00:48:02,525
It is a very common name in Korea.

777
00:48:05,395 --> 00:48:07,894
Hey, if you search for Kim Min Su...

778
00:48:07,895 --> 00:48:10,395
on social media, there are thousands of them.

779
00:48:11,595 --> 00:48:13,335
Are you telling me to search through all those thousands of people?

780
00:48:14,105 --> 00:48:15,105
Are you crazy?

781
00:48:15,465 --> 00:48:16,475
We have no choice.

782
00:48:16,975 --> 00:48:18,405
This is the best option in this situation.

783
00:48:19,235 --> 00:48:20,644
If we find that director, we can clear...

784
00:48:20,645 --> 00:48:22,875
Ji An's rumour from the power abuse accusation.

785
00:48:23,345 --> 00:48:25,315
Oh, I don't know. Hey, why do I have to do that?

786
00:48:25,645 --> 00:48:26,984
- Because... - I am not doing this...

787
00:48:26,985 --> 00:48:28,585
as a former fan club president.

788
00:48:30,385 --> 00:48:32,455
- Because you are my brother. - What?

789
00:48:33,015 --> 00:48:34,725
Dong Gyeong!

790
00:48:37,555 --> 00:48:38,555
Add the honorific.

791
00:48:40,995 --> 00:48:45,235
My dear Dong Gyeong.

792
00:48:45,935 --> 00:48:50,335
Every time something happens, you always find me.

793
00:48:51,305 --> 00:48:53,775
I will take a look.

794
00:48:57,115 --> 00:48:58,375
Why are you working so hard?

795
00:49:01,045 --> 00:49:02,245
Are you really going to switch to being a manager?

796
00:49:02,615 --> 00:49:04,555
Are you crazy?

797
00:49:05,555 --> 00:49:06,555
Then what is it?

798
00:49:10,295 --> 00:49:11,425
Just...

799
00:49:18,335 --> 00:49:20,635
I thought breaking up with someone who is smiling...

800
00:49:21,565 --> 00:49:22,735
would hurt less.

801
00:49:24,005 --> 00:49:25,505
Oh, you fool.

802
00:49:26,575 --> 00:49:28,305
Why would you break up with someone who is smiling?

803
00:49:29,575 --> 00:49:30,775
How sad.

804
00:49:37,115 --> 00:49:39,685
They say the two of them were close from the beginning.

805
00:49:40,185 --> 00:49:41,854
Our CEO as an entertainment CEO.

806
00:49:41,855 --> 00:49:43,595
And Reporter Han as a paid journalist.

807
00:49:45,525 --> 00:49:46,725
A paid journalist?

808
00:49:46,825 --> 00:49:48,295
A journalist who writes articles for money.

809
00:49:49,095 --> 00:49:50,434
He makes potential artists to be famous...

810
00:49:50,435 --> 00:49:51,865
and sends away those unnecessary ones.

811
00:49:53,435 --> 00:49:55,435
So, there were only articles about Yu Ji An...

812
00:49:55,835 --> 00:49:57,435
in his recently written articles.

813
00:49:57,975 --> 00:50:00,074
If a paid reporter publishes a few articles,

814
00:50:00,075 --> 00:50:01,904
the paid commenters rush in and shape public opinion...

815
00:50:01,905 --> 00:50:03,574
in the desired direction.

816
00:50:03,575 --> 00:50:04,815
That is how it works.

817
00:50:05,715 --> 00:50:07,984
Anyway, Reporter Han's wealth accumulation...

818
00:50:07,985 --> 00:50:10,215
was thanks to our CEO.

819
00:50:14,525 --> 00:50:18,354
So, Counsellor, do you think the culprit who ruined Ji An...

820
00:50:18,355 --> 00:50:20,165
was my boss?

821
00:50:21,665 --> 00:50:22,665
As you can see,

822
00:50:22,666 --> 00:50:24,195
it is just a suspicion based on circumstantial evidence.

823
00:50:25,995 --> 00:50:27,435
I...

824
00:50:27,735 --> 00:50:29,265
I think...

825
00:50:32,605 --> 00:50:33,705
Oh, it's nothing.

826
00:50:36,375 --> 00:50:40,344
One more thing, our CEO is reporting about Ji An...

827
00:50:40,345 --> 00:50:41,345
somewhere.

828
00:50:42,285 --> 00:50:43,285
Reporting?

829
00:50:43,955 --> 00:50:44,955
To whom?

830
00:50:45,185 --> 00:50:47,225
I don't know that.

831
00:50:48,185 --> 00:50:49,655
Manager Kim didn't know either.

832
00:50:49,925 --> 00:50:52,654
Is it an unofficial power broker? A mastermind?

833
00:50:52,655 --> 00:50:53,725
That is all he said.

834
00:50:57,665 --> 00:50:58,695
But what is that?

835
00:50:59,195 --> 00:51:00,905
Someone is sitting and someone is standing.

836
00:51:02,805 --> 00:51:06,235
Oh, it is like a rule in our industry.

837
00:51:07,005 --> 00:51:09,775
The lead actors sit, and the supporting actors stand.

838
00:51:10,445 --> 00:51:12,875
This must be Ji An's first time experiencing something like this.

839
00:51:13,615 --> 00:51:15,714
If it had been the old days, Ji An would have mentioned...

840
00:51:15,715 --> 00:51:17,414
about her class and she would have flipped the set.

841
00:51:17,415 --> 00:51:18,854
And she would have just gone home immediately...

842
00:51:18,855 --> 00:51:21,025
if she had felt bad.

843
00:51:22,155 --> 00:51:23,355
She has changed a lot.

844
00:51:24,255 --> 00:51:25,625
What is popularity?

845
00:51:27,295 --> 00:51:28,295
Indeed.

846
00:51:29,595 --> 00:51:30,995
She has changed so much.

847
00:51:31,835 --> 00:51:33,735
Alright, we will resume filming.

848
00:51:40,445 --> 00:51:41,445
Let's move.

849
00:51:47,185 --> 00:51:48,185
Ready.

850
00:51:49,315 --> 00:51:50,515
Action.

851
00:51:51,355 --> 00:51:54,225
Because of the promotion card the president gave you?

852
00:51:54,655 --> 00:51:55,855
Just for that?

853
00:51:56,125 --> 00:51:57,195
What are you talking about, senior?

854
00:51:58,295 --> 00:52:00,794
You are the one who is doing this...

855
00:52:00,795 --> 00:52:03,335
for a promotion.

856
00:52:05,995 --> 00:52:07,135
Hello, Detective. What's up?

857
00:52:08,035 --> 00:52:09,035
Then you know well?

858
00:52:09,735 --> 00:52:12,375
How you ruined the hard work of many people.

859
00:52:13,305 --> 00:52:14,505
This is your last chance.

860
00:52:15,845 --> 00:52:20,515
- Okay, then let's meet tomorrow. - Cut, cut!

861
00:52:25,755 --> 00:52:28,255
Ji An, your acting is so good this time.

862
00:52:28,755 --> 00:52:31,025
– Really? – It is better than expected.

863
00:52:31,525 --> 00:52:33,825
Let's continue shooting the next scene without needing another take.

864
00:52:34,525 --> 00:52:35,525
Yes.

865
00:53:55,545 --> 00:53:57,275
(Dong Gyeong Kitchen)

866
00:53:59,075 --> 00:54:00,085
Yes, welcome.

867
00:54:04,785 --> 00:54:07,525
Oh, Ji An, it has been a while.

868
00:54:11,955 --> 00:54:13,355
Please, have some tea.

869
00:54:16,225 --> 00:54:17,235
Oh, my.

870
00:54:18,395 --> 00:54:19,865
Well...

871
00:54:20,165 --> 00:54:23,735
I don't know much about Eun Hwan's father's accident.

872
00:54:24,975 --> 00:54:26,035
It's a forbidden topic.

873
00:54:27,145 --> 00:54:31,275
You don't know what kind of accident caused his death?

874
00:54:31,875 --> 00:54:33,715
Yes, you know.

875
00:54:34,215 --> 00:54:36,315
Eun Hwan feels guilty about that accident.

876
00:54:37,755 --> 00:54:39,614
He does not bring it up first,

877
00:54:39,615 --> 00:54:41,325
so I felt awkward asking him about it.

878
00:54:42,725 --> 00:54:43,824
What I know is that...

879
00:54:43,825 --> 00:54:47,795
Song Hwan was also injured in that accident.

880
00:54:49,165 --> 00:54:50,365
Even his sister...

881
00:54:52,495 --> 00:54:54,464
Then she became disabled...

882
00:54:54,465 --> 00:54:56,435
because of that accident?

883
00:54:57,005 --> 00:54:59,635
Yes, and after that,

884
00:55:00,645 --> 00:55:03,774
Eun Hwan suffered a lot.

885
00:55:03,775 --> 00:55:06,015
His suffering was beyond words.

886
00:55:06,715 --> 00:55:07,715
That's about it.

887
00:55:08,515 --> 00:55:12,355
Eun Hwan must have had a very hard time.

888
00:55:15,625 --> 00:55:16,625
Isn't it obvious?

889
00:55:17,295 --> 00:55:19,754
His mother was gone, his father passed away,

890
00:55:19,755 --> 00:55:20,995
and his sister was injured.

891
00:55:21,725 --> 00:55:23,835
He practically lived as a young head of household.

892
00:55:24,895 --> 00:55:27,365
Now, he is doing well on his own,

893
00:55:27,765 --> 00:55:29,204
but that guy has a heartbreaking life story...

894
00:55:29,205 --> 00:55:31,335
that would make you cry.

895
00:55:33,105 --> 00:55:34,244
How can you go on a private schedule...

896
00:55:34,245 --> 00:55:35,805
without the manager's permission?

897
00:55:38,945 --> 00:55:40,784
Did you forget that tomorrow is the day...

898
00:55:40,785 --> 00:55:41,815
of highlight scene filming?

899
00:55:59,065 --> 00:56:00,705
Is there any emotion you don't understand?

900
00:56:05,605 --> 00:56:07,305
No, not really.

901
00:56:13,915 --> 00:56:17,455
But why did Su Ji leave Jun Ho?

902
00:56:18,515 --> 00:56:19,715
She said she loved him.

903
00:56:21,325 --> 00:56:23,055
She probably left him...

904
00:56:23,603 --> 00:56:24,743
because she loved him.

905
00:56:27,125 --> 00:56:30,665
- Why are you asking it? - That does not make sense.

906
00:56:31,435 --> 00:56:32,895
Leaving because you love someone.

907
00:56:33,965 --> 00:56:36,105
If you love someone, you should stay with them no matter what.

908
00:56:38,135 --> 00:56:43,105
Even if being together makes you both unhappy?

909
00:56:44,115 --> 00:56:47,445
Why would you be unhappy with someone you love?

910
00:56:48,185 --> 00:56:49,745
Not being together is what makes you unhappy.

911
00:56:53,285 --> 00:56:57,955
Because it could be a love that can never come true.

912
00:57:04,765 --> 00:57:06,794
If it can never come true,

913
00:57:06,795 --> 00:57:10,634
then being together would only be a punishment for each other,

914
00:57:10,635 --> 00:57:12,375
wouldn't it?

915
00:57:14,905 --> 00:57:15,905
You're lying.

916
00:57:18,075 --> 00:57:19,514
Where is there such a thing as a love...

917
00:57:19,515 --> 00:57:20,685
that can never come true in this world?

918
00:57:21,545 --> 00:57:23,854
Those are just excuses made...

919
00:57:23,855 --> 00:57:25,785
by people who want to cowardly run away.

920
00:57:27,625 --> 00:57:31,125
If I love someone, I will never leave them.

921
00:57:32,953 --> 00:57:34,263
I will stay by their side no matter what.

922
00:57:36,195 --> 00:57:39,665
And I will never forgive anyone...

923
00:57:42,235 --> 00:57:43,835
who says they love me and then leaves.

924
00:57:44,705 --> 00:57:45,705
Never.

